<p><strong>Parallelism</strong>—Two or more parallel statements or components, synonymous, complementary, or antithetical, that convey a scriptural message.</p>
<p><strong>Parity Covenant</strong>—A covenant between equals as in the concept of “one for all and all for one” that characterizes God&rsquo;s end-time servants.</p>
<p><strong>Passover</strong>—Deliverance from the tenth plague God sent on Egypt that led to Israel&rsquo;s release from bondage, which Jews and others celebrate annually.</p>
