<p><strong>Restitution</strong>—A just repayment or compensation for transgression, whether paid by the offender or by a proxy savior who assumes the debt.</p>
<p><strong>Restoration</strong>—In Hebrew prophecy, the reinstitution of all the positive features of Israel&rsquo;s past that were lost on account of transgression.</p>
<p><strong>Resurrection</strong>—Based on Jehovah&rsquo;s proxy salvation, the physical raising from death to life on a spiritual level matching one&rsquo;s righteousness or wickedness.</p>
