<p><strong>Sabbath Day</strong>—The seventh day of the week, a day of rest from work, whose observance is a measure of one&rsquo;s keeping God&rsquo;s covenant.</p>
<p><strong>Sacrifice</strong>—(1) Under the Mosaic Code, an animal&rsquo;s life in place of a transgressor&rsquo;s; (2) under a higher law, a proxy savior&rsquo;s offering of himself.</p>
<p><strong>Salvation</strong>—The state of being redeemed from all evil, temporal and spiritual, by Jehovah God of Israel, who personifies salvation.</p>
